         <div type="translation">
            <p>This is the memorial of Poseides, son of Herakleides, righteous man. And he wronged no one ever. And if anyone has the power to see and speak good, to him may the gods be gracious; and may he do nothing wrong. And if someone desecrates this memorial or these plants or figures or if (someone) should carry into this memorial any other body, except mine and that of my wife and of my sons and daughters, themselves, and if someone should carry off this memorial for the purpose of sureties or should himself buy or assign to others or carry another body into (the tomb) unless he himself (Poseides) specify the above in respect to the memorial; and if anyone either perpetrates despiteful treatment or (exerts) physical force on this (monument), (then) Artemis Medea and Ephesia and all the gods (transitive verb implied) him and his descendants. (from Getty Museum web entry)</p>
         </div>
